Create a new directory and virtual environment:  
mkdir blog_app
cd blog_app
python3 -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate  # on Windows use `venv\Scripts\activate`
Install Flask and necessary libraries:
pip install Flask Flask-SQLAlchemy Flask-WTF
Setup project directory structure:
blog_app/
├── app/
│   ├── __init__.py
│   ├── models.py
│   ├── routes.py
│   ├── forms.py
│   ├── templates/
│   │   ├── base.html
│   │   ├── index.html
│   │   ├── login.html
│   │   ├── register.html
│   │   ├── post.html
│   │   ├── new_post.html
│   │   └── edit_post.html
├── venv/
├── config.py
├── run.py
└── README.md
Write source code for the application:

config.py: Configuration for Flask application.
app/__init__.py: Initialize the Flask app and configure routes.
app/models.py: Define database structure (User, Post).
app/routes.py: Define routes and handling logic.
app/forms.py: Define forms using Flask-WTF.
Templates in app/templates/: HTML files for user interface.
